@node PROGHISTORY "Historie vìvoje programu VisualPrefs"

HISTORIE PROGRAMU VISUALPREFS
=============================

@{i}@{b}@{FG shine}Ponechêno v originêle @{FG text}@{ub}@{ui}


@{b}1.4 (23.7.98)@{ub}

Bug-fixes:

ñ Added a workaround for a bug in graphics.library/BltMaskBitMapRastPort()
  which caused system gadgets to appear as garbage when Birdie compatibility
  was enabled on interleaved 8-bit screens.

ñ Added a workaround for a bug in CyberGraphX which causes line drawing to
  sometimes produce different results than expected when the PLANES2FAST
  option is turned on. This was affecting especially the shape of XEN arrows.

ñ Corrected a couple of errors in the appearance of horizontal arrows in
  the "Standard" style.

ñ Now window titles should no longer be drawn twice (and out of phase) when
  the PowerWB patch is running.

ñ Fixed a bug in the rendering of window titlebars when Birdie is running.

ñ Now the GUI editor always checks the version of catalog files.

ñ Fixed a bug which caused the Draw() function to be called with an illegal
  -1 coordinate when applying the KingCON patch.

ñ Now VisualPrefs checks if a screen can actually be closed before removing
  its patches. This should solve most problems of "GUI reverting to normal"
  which happened with programs such as WebDesign and Cinema4D.

ñ When using MagicMenu in non-blocking mode, window titlebars covered by a
  menu no longer have their title refreshed at the wrong position after the
  menu closes.

ñ Cycle gadgets in "Future/Flat" style had their symbol rendered with a wrong
  color when pressed if the gadget frame didn't use the Fill pen for its
  background in "selected" state. Now fixed.

Enhancements:

ñ Now cycle gadgets can display a pop-up menu when pressed! The behavior of
  the pop-up menu can be configured with the GUI editor (sorry, no preview
  yet). You can even set a delay for the pop-up menu to wait before appearing,
  so that with "quick" clicks the cycle gadget will still behave like usual.
  Please @{"read the guide" link POPUPGADGETS} for more information.

ñ Disabled GadTools button and cycle gadgets can now be displayed with a
  new 3D look (without ghosting and with their text recessed). You can also
  choose the colors to be used for this.

ñ GadTools button and cycle gadgets can now "shift" their contents when
  pressed (like scroller arrows already did).

ñ Now "Future" style border gadgets can optionally be made to only react to
  clicks made within the actual "button" image, rather than the ones made
  on the whole gadget hit box.

ñ You can now choose a XEN look for GadTools gadgets without affecting
  all other 3D frames in the system (although of course you can still do
  it the old way, too).

ñ Now you can have compatibility with Birdie on all screens, not just the
  Workbench one. The way to configure it HAS CHANGED, please @{"read the guide!" link NOTES}
  It now also involves setting an option in the GUI editor.

ñ Now the titlebar of screen can be made fully 3D, by adding the missing
  "bright" edge at the left and top sides. A new pen (Bar Contour) has been
  added to this purpose.

ñ You can now set the color of inactive window titles.

ñ The IM_FRAMEBOX method of "frameiclass" now reflects the real thickness
  of the frame borders.

ñ The "PatchWB" program by Thomas Richter has been added to the VisualPrefs
  distribution archive; it should fix the annoying Workbench screen re-open
  lock-up problem once and for all, by killing its real cause. Thanks Thomas!

ñ At last, you can install a proper 68060 version of VisualPrefs and GUI.

ñ Now the installation script allows you to choose whether to install icons
  or not, so you can avoid overwriting your existing icons.

ñ The GUI editor now embeds a version number in the preferences file when
  saving. This will make much easier in future releases the addition of new
  features without loss of compatibility.


@{b}1.3c (30.12.97)@{ub}

Small update:

ñ Fixed a bug which caused Enforcer hits at the opening of Workbench windows
  when the PowerWB patch was running.

ñ DirOpus iconify & padlock gadgets should now be patched whichever window
  they appear in; previously some windows were missed by VisualPrefs.

ñ Now the GUI editor saves a "palette.prefs" file with default settings if
  one doesn't exist.


@{b}1.3b (15.12.97)@{ub}

Small update:

ñ Compatibility with Birdie in hi-color and true-color modes was broken
  due to the previous bug-fix. Now it works again.


@{b}1.3a (12.12.97)@{ub}

Small update:

ñ Fixed an odd bug which prevented VisualPrefs from running on most V39
  (Kickstart 3.0) systems.

ñ Slightly modified the documentation.


@{b}1.3 (26.11.97)@{ub}

Bug-fixes:

ñ Fixed a bug that caused the YAM mailer to display fake error messages.

ñ Now the iconify gadget of the DirOpus text reader window is also patched.

ñ The DirOpus screen title wasn't always vertically centered. Now fixed.

ñ Removed an Enforcer hit with DirOpus 4.

ñ Now the additional titlebar gadgets (such as the MUI ones) have the correct
  colors on Picasso96 hicolor and truecolor screens.

ñ The previous fix for the YAM problem, found on my home page, did cause
  address errors on plain 68000 CPUs. Now fixed.

ñ With big titlebar gadgets, sometimes the window title covered part of the
  gadget at its immediate right. Now fixed.

ñ Saving the preferences doesn't corrupt anymore the titlebar of some screens
  if they have an increased titlebar height.

ñ Now deadlocks at the reopening of the Workbench screen when saving the
  preferences should be less likely to happen.

Enhancements:

ñ Now VisualPrefs can be made nearly 100% compatible with Birdie! See the
  documentation to learn how to obtain this.

ñ Now the KingCON patch also works for RAW: and KRAW:.

ñ Now VisualPrefs also patches the Scalos iconify gadget image.

ñ Added some developer documentation about the "tbiclass" image class.


@{b}1.2a (22.10.97)@{ub}

Small update:

ñ Fixed a bug in the installation script.

ñ The "Flat" screen depth gadget image now uses the Bar Detail pen if the
  Glyph pen and the Bar Block pen have the same value.

ñ Fixed a bug in the look of the inactive "padlock" image in the "Standard"
  style.


@{b}1.2 (18.10.97)@{ub}

Bug-fixes:

ñ The patch for the ClassAct iconify gadget didn't work with the latest
  release of ClassAct. Now this is fixed.

ñ The workaround for the V39 gadtools.library bug didn't work very well,
  so I found another one.

Enhancements:

ñ Now VisualPrefs patches DirOpus 5.5+ titlebar gadgets. Only tried it with
  Magellan, but it should work also with previous releases. Hope you like the
  new "padlock" image...

ñ Renamed "iconifyimageclass" to "tbiclass" to comply with the new API of
  ViNCEd. Now VisualPrefs should be 100% compatible with ViNCEd (3.53+).

ñ Now you can choose to install a 68020/030 or 68040/060 version of
  VisualPrefs and GUI.

ñ Some optimizations to the code of certain patches.

ñ Of course, this release also contains all the changes introduced in
  release 1.1, which wasn't released on Aminet (see below).


@{b}1.1 (3.10.97)@{ub}

Some bug-fixes:

ñ No more crashes with MUI "screen close" gadgets.

ñ The screen titlebar doesn't get corrupted anymore under CyberGraphX 3
  with the SUPERLAYERS option on.

ñ The GUI editor now correctly fills the bottom scroller's hole in the
  preview area if you select the "Fill recessed areas..." option.

ñ Now the GUI editor allows for fonts with an height smaller than 7 pixels;
  the new limit is 5 pixels.

ñ GadTools arrow gadgets didn't get patched if their width or height was
  smaller than 10 pixels; now the limit is 9 pixels.

ñ The image of CheckBox gadgets sometimes did overwrite part of the border.

ñ Added a workaround for a bug in the V39 gadtools.library concerning the
  displaying of the contents of number gadgets. Hope it works!

ñ The "Global" menu is now correctly updated when you select "Last saved"
  from the "Edit" menu.

Enhancements:

ñ The rendering of MUI titlebar gadgets should now be somewhat faster.

ñ Added a patch for MagicMenu 2.19+ allowing to vertically center the
  menu titles in the screen bar.

ñ Added the possibility to inhibit the use of the Template.

ñ Added public "iconifyimageclass" image class for use by programs such
  as ViNCEd.


@{b}1.0a (26.7.97)@{ub}

Small update:

ñ Fixed some bugs in the installation script.

ñ Added a few more safety controls in the GUI editor.

ñ There were some cases in which the Workbench screen would lock up
  if closed and reopened. Now this shouldn't happen anymore.

ñ Slightly modified the documentation.


@{b}1.0 (23.7.97)@{ub}

First Aminet release.


@{b}Beta releases #1 to #7@{ub}

Private beta-tester releases.

@endnode

